.
<gloss>When they had eaten and were sewing moccasins or mending such as were torn, Sweet-Grass arose and went off alone.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.6">
<w canon="êwako" class="pr" gcat="PR" sgloss="that_one" stem="êwako">êwakôw</w>
<w canon="ayinânêwosâp" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="eighteen" stem="ayinânêwosâp">ayênâniwosâp</w>
<w canon="ê-tahtopiponwêt" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="be_so_old" stem="tahtopiponwê" suffix="-t">êh-tahtopiponwêt</w>
<w canon="awa" class="dem" gcat="3sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa">awa</w>
<w canon="kâ-sipwêhtêt" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj" sgloss="leave" stem="sipwêhtê" suffix="-t">kâ-sipwêhtêt</w>
,
<w canon="ê-wî-kakwê-wâpamât" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj wî|will kakwê|try_to" sgloss="see" stem="wâpam" suffix="-ât">ê-wîh-kakwê-wâpamât</w>
<w canon="ayahciyiniwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="Blackfoot" stem="ayahciyiniw" suffix="-a">iyâhciyiniwah</w>
.
<gloss>Eighteen years old was he when he then set out to see Blackfoot.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.7">
<w canon="ôki" class="dem" gcat="3pDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa" suffix="-3p">ôki</w>
<w canon="wiya" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="WIYA" stem="wiya">wiya</w>
<w canon="kotakak" class="pr" gcat="3pPR" sgloss="other" stem="kotak" suffix="-3p">kotakak</w>
<w canon="apiwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="sit" stem="api" suffix="-wak">apiwak</w>
.
<gloss>Meanwhile the others stayed where they were.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.8">
<w canon="ê-asawâpit" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="be_on_lookout" stem="asawâpi" suffix="-t">êh-asawâpit</w>
